[h4 id=Kanto 
	" Kanto
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"All of Kanto is done without refreshing PP once, so it's again important to plan which move to use where, sometimes incurring avoidable crits in order to preserve PP.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"On the SS Aqua, we encounter the only time the gender affects the gameplay in any way during this run, by prompting the rescued girl to emit 5 additional characters of dialog.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"After landing in Kanto, it's faster to fly to Vermilion rather than biking from the pier.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Kanto is fairly open and allows for lots of different routes and possibilities.
	$LF
	"The general strategy is to do the Gyms whenever they are closest on our way through the main Kanto story line of bringing the Power Plant back online.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"There are multiple different optimal paths through Sabrina's teleport maze.
	$LF
	"I use two different ones for in and out.
	$LF
	"It's also notable that there's a route with fewer teleports, but more walking time, which ends up slower.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"After running into the Rocket in Misty's Gym, it's not actually necessary to collect it in order to enable the Misty cutscene in Route 25, and it turns out to be faster to do it later.
	$LF
	"Also, all trainer fights in Misty's Gym can be skipped by surfing around them.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Even though the player starts in Vermilion, the Gym is closest only on our second visit before clearing the Snorlax, so I slot it Surge there.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Brock is just a small detour after exiting Diglett's Cave.
	$LF
	"You need to at least visit Pewter City so that it's possible to fly back there later, but at that point it's faster to just do the Gym there and then.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Blue is the last Gym because Crunch is required to OHKO Exeggutor, and Arcanine can only be OHKO'd using Spark at level 61 or above.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Red 
	" Red
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Red has multiple Pokémon which won't KO in one turn, but using X items would not have reduced the total number of turns required, so it was not worth shopping for.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Red's Espeon gets fully paralyzed to avoid it using Psychic, which would cost even more time, partly due to the bugged Special Defense badge stat boost.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Red's Snorlax only is a two turn KO thanks to the side effect of Iron Tail, lowering its defense and enabling the badge stat boost on the second turn.
	$LF
	"Red's Venusaur is the same case as the Snorlax, but with Crunch and lowering the Special Defense instead.
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Anoteontimingandconsoleverification 
	" A note on timing and console verification
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"While this page states this run's time is 2:48:50, the actual time it would take when played back on console is 2:48:39.703.
	$LF
	"The reason for this is that the concept of a "frame" is variable on a GB, and BizHawk's input frames don't align with them, yet it calculates time as if they were evenly spaced.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Unfortunately, this same discrepancy makes a console verification of this run rather unlikely, because of the real-time clock.
	$LF
	"Since BizHawk's frames are longer, and its emulated RTC is bound to the number of frames, its RTC ticks slightly faster than on an actual console, inevitably causing desyncs over time.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The correct solution to the RTC issue is probably to base BizHawk's RTC on the number of emitted audio samples instead, but I'm not sure it would solve all the problems with Gen II console verification.
	$LF
]p
